headline: Texas Instruments Says Data Centers, Industrial Recovery Driving Growth into First Quarter
summary: The semiconductor company said it expects earnings growth in the current quarter as data centers contribute more to sales and the industrial market recovers.

headline: PPG Industries Logs Higher Quarterly Revenue on Higher Prices, Volume
summary: The Pittsburgh paint and coatings company’s revenue grew around 5% to $3.91 billion in the fourth quarter.

headline: Texas Instruments Sales Rise, But Profit Slips
summary: The semiconductor company posted a profit of $1.16 billion, or $1.27 a share, compared with $1.21 billion, or $1.30 a share, a year earlier.

headline: LVMH CEO Signals Caution for Luxury Sector in 2026 Despite Quarterly Sales Growth
summary: LVMH shares a mixed outlook for the luxury industry after full-year organic revenue dipped across key segments like fashion and spirits.

headline: Booz Allen Stock Dips 8.1% Since Fiscal Q3 Earnings Release
summary: BAH stock beats Q3 EPS estimates but misses on revenues, trims FY26 sales outlook, and shares dip 8.1% after the Jan. 23 earnings release.

headline: Home Prices Surprise on the Upside, With 1.4% Increase
summary: Prices in an index tracking changes in 20 large metropolitan areas rose 1.4% from a year prior, compared with the prior month’s 1.3% gain.  While the reading bucked expectations that called for a tenth straight month of cooling in the 20-city index, price growth remained “tepid” in the broader context, Nicholas Godec, S&P Dow Jones Indices’ head of fixed income tradables and commodities, said in a statement.  “Home price growth still trails inflation by roughly 1.3 percentage points, meaning real home values have effectively edged down over the past year,” he said.

headline: Sysco 2026 Adjusted Earnings Seen at High End of Range
summary: Sysco’s fiscal second-quarter net income fell, but the food-supplies giant said it was set to hit the high end of its previous full-year adjusted-earnings projection.

headline: Atlas Copco Expects Near-Term Demand to Remain at Current Level
summary: The industrial tool maker announced a higher dividend payout for the year as net profit and revenue dropped.

headline: What S&P Earnings Would Be Without The Magnificent Seven
summary: As a group, the Magnificent Seven are expected to report earnings growth of 20.3% for the fourth quarter.
